messages.message:
Going to watch this thread and add in @pauline.comising who is working on the devex package that will replace this script.

If there is any functionality regression, we'll want to make sure it's incorporated.
That package requires 23.07 with ibllm installed locally correct @pauline.comising

Yes, it won't address this current issue as I know Amelia is developing in 23.04 sandbox.

The package will be available by default starting in 23.07 with all required services for sandboxes and SaaS environments (with customer acceptance).
@amelia.bruno lets confirm the version and then we can deep dive from there
@amelia.bruno +1 to Josh's comment. You may need to re-create the weaviate index after incrementing the model_version used by the prompt API
yea that worked :slightly_smiling_face: I had to delete the cached files on aihub.uat so that the script would create a new index
thanks for your help @joshbronko and @Matt Weaver
btw @joshbronko you might want to update the llm model version to 1.1.17 in the script on github
We can set it at the top, ill update it now. thanks for the headsup
Okay so the code looks to be okay, just needed to leverage 1.1.17 and the index was probably written in the older version
yea the index was just because I ran it in 1.1.16 earlier and it was using the cached index after I changed it to 1.1.17
Team, should we consider having an warning message stating that the index was ran on an older version of the ibllm when using a newer one to run inference against it?
Maybe even just re-index when we detect that this is the case?
